g.text: CloudFormation resources are the AWS components (like EC2 instances, S3 buckets, Lambda functions, etc.) that you want to create
and manage in you AWS environment.
* Resources type identifiers are of the form:
- Resources: is the section where you define all the resources.
- MyEC2Instance: is the logical name of the resource
- Type: specifies the type of resource (e.g: AWS::EC2::Instance)
- Properties: Includes the configuration details of the resource, like the instance type and AMI ID
* Few AWS services are not supported by CloudFormation for that you can use CloudFormation Custom Resources
